content: I mean, I think back in October, we just weren't really seeing a lot of great opportunities at pricing that made a lot of sense, still acquiring kind of $90 million or so in the fourth quarter and getting above the $480 million, which was the guidance that we  (ph) during that call shows that it did come back enough for us to be able to deploy that capital, and we're seeing a better backdrop now, and more sellers that are willing to kind of adjust their pricing to current market conditions.
